  "prompt": "How does one start a technical society in a college in India?",
  "response": "To start a technical society in a college in India, follow these steps:\n\n1. Initial Planning\n- Identify the specific technical domain (e.g., coding, robotics, AI)\n- Define clear objectives and goals\n- Create a preliminary structure for the society\n\n2. Seek College Approval\n- Approach the department head or college administration\n- Prepare a detailed proposal explaining the society's purpose\n- Get formal permission and recognition from the college\n\n3. Form a Core Team\n- Recruit passionate and skilled students\n- Assign roles like president, vice president, secretary\n- Ensure representation from different years/branches\n\n4. Documentation\n- Draft a constitution/bylaws\n- Create membership guidelines\n- Define event and activity protocols\n\n5. Registration Process\n- Register with college administration\n- Create official documentation\n- Set up a formal organizational structure\n\n6. Funding and Resources\n- Request initial funding from college\n- Explore sponsorship opportunities\n- Apply for college/department grants\n\n7. Activities and Events\n- Organize workshops\n- Conduct technical seminars\n- Host hackathons\n- Arrange guest lectures\n- Participate in inter-college competitions\n\n8. Promotion\n- Use social media\n- Create posters\n- Conduct awareness campaigns\n- Recruit new members\n\n9. Networking\n- Connect with industry professionals\n- Collaborate with other technical societies\n- Attend external technical events\n\n10. Continuous Improvement\n- Regular feedback\n- Annual review of society's performance\n- Update strategies and goals",
